## Content Structure
- Organize content by type and category
- Use consistent naming conventions for content files
- Use front matter for metadata
- Use YAML for structured data
- Use markdown for long-form content

## Markdown Usage
- Use proper heading hierarchy (h1, h2, h3, etc.)
- Use lists for grouped information
- Use code blocks with language specification
- Use tables for structured data
- Use images with proper alt text

## Front Matter
- Include title, description, and date in front matter
- Use tags and categories for content organization
- Include SEO metadata in front matter
- Use custom fields for specific content types
- Keep front matter consistent across similar content

## Content Querying
- Use `queryContent()` for content retrieval
- Implement proper filtering and sorting
- Use pagination for large content collections
- Cache content queries when appropriate
- Implement proper error handling for content queries

## Content Rendering
- Use the `<ContentDoc>` component for single documents
- Use the `<ContentList>` component for content collections
- Use the `<ContentRenderer>` component for custom rendering
- Implement proper loading and error states
- Use content transformers for custom content processing

## SEO
- Include proper meta tags for content pages
- Implement proper canonical URLs
- Use structured data for rich snippets
- Implement proper Open Graph tags
- Use proper heading structure for SEO

## Performance
- Optimize images in content
- Use lazy loading for content components
- Implement proper caching strategies
- Use static generation for content pages
- Optimize content queries for performance